# Cloudflare Pages security headers — applied to every route.
# Docs: https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/headers/
#
# These three headers are safe and reversible: they only add browser-side
# protections and cannot break how the site loads or looks.
#
# Intentionally NOT included here:
#   - Strict-Transport-Security (HSTS): the "preload" form is near-permanent
#     and hard to undo. If wanted, enable HSTS from the Cloudflare dashboard
#     (SSL/TLS → Edge Certificates → HSTS), which is easy to turn back off.
#   - Content-Security-Policy: powerful but can silently break resources if
#     mis-tuned. Best added later in report-only mode first, then enforced.
/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: accelerometer=(), camera=(), display-capture=(), geolocation=(), gyroscope=(), magnetometer=(), microphone=(), payment=(), usb=(), browsing-topics=()
